<h2>
    <a href="/blog/illustrating-the-padovan-sequence/">Illustrating the Padovan sequence</a>
</h2>




<h6 class="post-meta">
    Posted by:
    
    <a href="/blog/author/christian/">christian</a>
    
    
    
    in
    
    <a href="/blog/category/featured-on-frontpage/">Featured on frontpage</a>
    
    
    
    on 8 Apr 2020
</h6>





<a href="/blog/illustrating-the-padovan-sequence/">
    <img class="img-thumbnail pull-left" src="/static/media/uploads/blog/padovan/.thumbnails/padovan.png/padovan-90x90.png">
</a>





<p>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Padovan_sequence">Padovan sequence</a> is a cousin of the more famous Fibonacci sequence defined by the initial values $P(1)=P(2)=P(3)=1$ and the recurrence relation $P(n) = P(n-2) + P(n-3)$. That is, the next value is obtained not by summing the previous two values but by summing the two values before the last one. The first few values are:</p>




